"Your interruption, however, has altered the equation. Direct acquisition is no longer optimal. The new protocol is... sterilization."
He reached over his shoulder. With a wet clack, he twisted the primary valve on the rig bolted to his spine. A jet of green steam vented violently from his neck seals. The tubes running into his shoulders glowed bright, angry red as combat stimulants flooded his system. His muscles swelled against the bolts holding his armor in place.
He drew a Daedric Warhammer from his backΓÇöa slab of black metal that looked less like a weapon and more like a bridge support. He rested the head on the ground, and the impact shook the entire room.
"I will not abide contaminants in my workspace."

PART II: THE BREAKER FALLS
